A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to public utilities; requiring stays of
2 proceedings of the public service commission pending the
3 resolution of lawsuits as specified; providing exemptions;
4 making conforming amendments; specifying applicability; and
5 providing for an effective date.
6
7 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
8
9 Section 1. W.S. 37-2-130 and 37-2-214 are amended to
10 read:
11
12 37-2-130. Right of review; stay of proceedings.
13
1 HB0218

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0394
1 (a) Subject to subsections (b) and (c) of this
2 section, a person adversely affected or aggrieved by any
3 action, findings, conclusions or decision of the public
4 service commission is entitled to judicial review thereof
5 according to the procedures established by the Wyoming
6 Administrative Procedure Act and the Wyoming Rules of
7 Appellate Procedure. The standards to be applied, to
8 judicial review proceedings, including scope of review,
9 shall be those standards established in the Wyoming
10 Administrative Procedure Act.
11
12 (b) If a public utility files a lawsuit that
13 challenges or seeks judicial review under this section by
14 challenging the constitutionality or legality of a
15 provision of this act or of a rule, regulation or procedure
16 of the commission, or that raises an argument under W.S.
17 16-3-114(c)(ii)(A) through (D), the commission shall stay
18 each request, application, rate case and any other matter
19 that requires application or consideration of the
20 challenged statute, rule, regulation or procedure until the
21 lawsuit or judicial review is fully resolved and closed.
22 This subsection shall apply to all requests, applications,
23 rate cases and other matters before the commission impacted
2 HB0218

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0394
1 by the challenged statute, rule, regulation or procedure or
2 that requires the application of the challenged statute,
3 rule, regulation or procedure, regardless of the party
4 involved in the request, application, rate case or matter.
5
6 (c) Subsection (b) of this section shall not apply
7 to:
8
9 (i) Any lawsuit or judicial review based on the
10 commission's application of facts or evidence or resolution
11 of disputed facts or evidence or based on an argument
12 raised under W.S. 16-3-114(c)(ii)(E);
13
14 (ii) Any action that the commission begins and
15 prosecutes for violations under W.S. 37-2-215.
16
17 37-2-214. Rehearing.
18
19 Subject to W.S. 37-2-130(b) and (c), at any time after
20 an order has been made by the commission any person
21 interested therein may apply for a rehearing in respect to
22 any matter determined therein and the commission shall
23 grant and hold a rehearing if in its judgment sufficient
3 HB0218

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0394
1 reason therefor be made to appear, which rehearing shall be
2 subject to rules as the commission may prescribe.
3 Applications for rehearing shall stay the effect of any
4 order or decision of the commission only as to the portion
5 of the order addressed in the rehearing application until
6 the commission denies the application or enters an order
7 following rehearing, whichever last occurs, provided,
8 however, that upon the request of any party and a showing
9 of good cause therefor, the commission may vacate the stay
10 and allow the order or decision to remain in effect. An
11 order or decision made after the rehearing vacating,
12 amending or modifying the original order or decision shall
13 not, as to the matter considered on rehearing, be open to a
14 further application for rehearing, and shall have the same
15 force and effect as the original order or decision.
16
17 Section 2. This act shall apply to all requests,
18 applications, rate cases and other matters filed with the
19 public service commission for which litigation specified in
20 this act has been filed before, on and after the effective
21 date of this act.
